snippet: Mr. Obama will arrive at an international economic meeting in Australia hoping to press European and Asian leaders to get their economies moving again — and perhaps buoy his own presidency.
abstract: Pres Obama will arrive at international economic meeting in Australia hoping to press European and Asian leaders to get their economies moving again and perhaps buoy his own foundering presidency; allies may be less than open to message if they question his ability to deliver his own promises in a reordered Washington.

byline.contributor: Jonathan Soble contributed reporting from Tokyo.

lead_paragraph: Mr. Obama will arrive at an international economic meeting in Australia hoping to press European and Asian leaders to get their economies moving again — and perhaps buoy his own presidency.

headline.main: Obama Aims to Lift the Global Economy, and Maybe Himself
headline.print_headline: Obama Aims to Lift Economy, and Maybe Himself
